2025-12-26 21:56:33,288 - debug_history - INFO - Generate history request body: {'messages': [{'id': '1766778834742', 'role': 'user', 'content': 'Based on my affordability and last 30 days spending, can I afford a used car installment? Keep it simple and show the trade-off.'}, {'id': 'd6ec0612-7152-4a23-8c9e-ad11e1ae6f44', 'role': 'assistant', 'content': '{"type": "text", "text": "Based on your financial profile, a **safe monthly car budget is ~750 AED**.\\n*(Includes loan, insurance, fuel, and maintenance buffer)*\\n\\n**Recommended Options:**\\n- **Used Toyota Yaris (2019)**\\n  - Price: 35,000 - 45,000 AED\\n  - Monthly All-in: ~900 - 1,100 AED\\n  - *Why: Most affordable, extremely low maintenance.*\\n\\n**Next Steps:**\\n1. **Refine**: Cash or Installments?\\n2. **Save to Plan**: Track this goal.\\n3. **Connect**: Link a dealer for real inventory."}'}, {'id': '1766778902480', 'role': 'user', 'content': 'What monthly payment would you cap me at and why?', 'date': '2025-12-26T19:55:02.480Z'}, {'id': '3da90eb2-b296-4789-b907-3734f2444bbb', 'role': 'assistant', 'content': '{"type": "viv_advice", "text": "As your Guardian of Wellbeing, I must cap your maximum monthly car-related expenses (payment, insurance, fuel, buffer) at **1,000 AED**. This is the highest threshold that keeps your current Financial Index (75.0) stable.\\n\\n**Why 1,000 AED?**\\n\\n1.  **The Pressure Point:** While 750 AED was the \'safe zone\' identified earlier, 1,000 AED is the limit before you significantly compromise your liquidity buffer. Maintaining this buffer is critical because you are currently operating in **Crisis Mode** (Health and Time Indexes are 0.0).\\n2.  **The Trade-Off:** Every dirham spent over the 750 AED safe limit reduces your flexibility to invest in your critical Health or Time reserves. If you encounter unexpected maintenance costs or need to buy back time (e.g., paying for delivery or services), a 1,000 AED commitment will make recovering your critical indexes much harder.\\n3.  **Future Target Impact:** Since you have no defined Life Goals, the immediate impact of this financial commitment will fall entirely on stabilizing your Vitals.", "data": {"summary": "Your absolute maximum responsible monthly payment cap is 1,000 AED.", "message_body": "As your Guardian of Wellbeing, I must cap your maximum monthly car-related expenses (payment, insurance, fuel, buffer) at **1,000 AED**. This is the highest threshold that keeps your current Financial Index (75.0) stable.\\n\\n**Why 1,000 AED?**\\n\\n1.  **The Pressure Point:** While 750 AED was the \'safe zone\' identified earlier, 1,000 AED is the limit before you significantly compromise your liquidity buffer. Maintaining this buffer is critical because you are currently operating in **Crisis Mode** (Health and Time Indexes are 0.0).\\n2.  **The Trade-Off:** Every dirham spent over the 750 AED safe limit reduces your flexibility to invest in your critical Health or Time reserves. If you encounter unexpected maintenance costs or need to buy back time (e.g., paying for delivery or services), a 1,000 AED commitment will make recovering your critical indexes much harder.\\n3.  **Future Target Impact:** Since you have no defined Life Goals, the immediate impact of this financial commitment will fall entirely on stabilizing your Vitals.", "viv_indexes": {"financial": {"current": 75.0, "delta": 0, "trend": "stable"}, "health": {"current": 0.0, "delta": 0, "trend": "stable"}, "time": {"current": 0.0, "delta": 0, "trend": "stable"}}, "goal_impact_analysis": "This decision currently acts as a stabilizing measure for the Financial Index (75.0). It has a high potential negative indirect impact on the critical Health (0.0) and Time (0.0) indexes by reducing flexibility.", "suggested_actions": ["Commit to finding a vehicle where the total monthly cost is closer to the 750 AED safe limit, not the 1,000 AED cap.", "Define a small Health Goal (e.g., \'1 hour of structured exercise per week\') to begin moving out of Crisis Mode before finalizing a major financial commitment.", "Input your existing monthly income to allow Viv to calculate a precise debt-to-income ratio (DTI) for better financial modeling."]}}', 'date': '2025-12-26T19:55:13.644211Z'}, {'id': '1766778993053', 'role': 'user', 'content': 'Add a goal: reduce discretionary spending by 10% next month.', 'date': '2025-12-26T19:56:33.053Z'}], 'context': {'location': {'lat': 29.98272, 'lng': 31.0673408}}, 'conversation_id': '888e5e98-79ad-4c53-8571-a79acd721ab6'}
